cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.SE 

This paper discusses a secure messaging application that uses decentralised storage servers and onion routing protocol to send end-to-end encrypted messages with minimal exposure of user metadata. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with secure communication. Additionally, the use of decentralised storage servers and onion routing protocol involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses privacy concerns and the protection of user metadata, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the messaging application, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
